<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="81" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID="http://zoobank.org/419F28D8-1962-4495-8B5A-670DF596CDA0" class="Gastropoda" family="Cochliopidae" genus="Mexicenotica" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mexicenotica" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Mexicenotica</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="2" pageNumber="81">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="81" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
The diagnostic features of the genus are the same as those of the type species 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Cochliopidae" genus="Mexicenotica" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mexicenotica xochii" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="xochii">Mexicenotica xochii</taxonomicName>
sp. n. The minute size with tear shaped shell and expanded oval aperture with a fragile flaring corrugated margin distinguish the new genus from any other related genera of 
<taxonomicName family="Cochliopidae" lsidName="" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" rank="family">Cochliopidae</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName family="Pomatiopsidae" lsidName="" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" rank="family">Pomatiopsidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="81" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
Named after the country of origin and cenotes, the specific vertical sinkhole karstic formations of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Yucatán´s">Yucatan's</normalizedToken>
plateau, whose phreatic waters and aquifers host the new genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
